SIMPLE: spirited
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Spirited
<hw>Spir"it*ed</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Animated or
possessed by a spirit.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧So talked the
<xex>spirited</xex>, sly snake.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Animated; full of life or vigor; lively; full of
spirit or fire; <as>as, a <ex>spirited</ex> oration; a <ex>spirited</ex>
answer</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ <xex>Spirited</xex> is much used in composition; as in
high-<xex>spirited</xex>, low-<xex>spirited</xex>,
mean-<xex>spirited</xex>, etc.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Lively; vivacious; animated; ardent; active;
bold; courageous.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Spir"it*ed*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Spir"it*ed*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spiritful</ent>⟦br⟧
